Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @salad potatoes{350%g} into 2cm chunks
(no need to peel) and place on a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle},
season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and toss to coat. Spread out on the
tray, then roast on the middle shelf of your oven until soft in the middle and
crispy on the outside, ~{30-35%minutes}. Shake the tray halfway through cooking.

Lay the @British chicken breasts{2} on a #chopping board{}, place your hand flat
on top and slice into it from the side (being careful not to slice all the way
through). Open it up like a book. Lay the chicken between two sheets of
#clingfilm{} and whack the chicken using the base of a #pan or a #rolling pin{}
until it's 1cm thick. Repeat for the other breast(s).

Slice open the @97% pork sausages{2}, remove the meat and discard the skin. Put
the meat in a #mixing bowl{} with the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} and stir. Place
the stuffing in a line across the long edge of each chicken breast (divide the
stuffing evenly!). Roll the chicken breast up tightly, enclosing the stuffing
inside.

> TIP: Secure the rolls with cocktail sticks if you have some.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the chicken
rolls with salt and pepper and fry for ~{5%minutes} until golden all over.
Transfer to another lined baking tray and roast on the top shelf of your oven,
~{15%minutes}.

> TIP: Don't wash the pan!

When the chicken is cooked, remove from the oven, cover with #foil{} and rest
for a few mins.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when the stuffing and chicken are no longer
> pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, boil your #kettle{}. Put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil for
the broccoli. Dissolve the @chicken stock powder{1/2%tsp} in a #measuring jug{}
of boiling @water{300%ml}.

Put the frying pan back on medium heat with a glug of oil and the @plain flour{8%g}.
Stir and cook until you have a thick paste, ~{1%minute} (this is a roux!). Whisk
in the stock bit by bit. Bring to a simmer and keep whisking. Cook until thickened
to your liking, ~{3-5%minutes}.

While the sauce cooks, add the @broccoli florets{200%g} to the pan of boiling
water and simmer until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a
#colander{}. Serve the stuffed chicken, roast potatoes and the broccoli with
a good helping of your pan sauce. Enjoy!